race.comment: ALL DRESSED UP (8) stuck on well last time to finish 0.8 lengths back in second (30.11) at this track in a Grade 5 over 520m. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Top prospect. BRUNSWICK DREAM (6) shapes well for this backing up an excellent 27.61 win with success at this track over 520m last time, recording 30.06. This tougher but expected to be in the finish. BATHTUB SPLASHER (1) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 4.5 lengths at Q Lakeside in a handy 19.52 beating King Roger. Boasts a strong record from this draw with three wins and two minor placings from six starts. Deserves serious consideration again. ZEPHYR (2) was in the money last time at this track (30.25) in a Grade 5, finishing a 2.75 lengths third. Has already won four times from this draw.
